
[1]countervail

   COUNTERVAIL, v.t. [counter and L., to avail or be strong.] To act
   against with equal force, or power; to equal; to act with equivalent
   effect against any thing; to balance; to compensate.

   The profit will hardly countervail the inconveniences.

   Although the enemy could not countervail the kings damage. Esther 7.

   COUNTERVAIL, n. Equal weight or strength; power or value sufficient to
     obviate any effect; equal weight or value; compensation; requital.
